<h2 id="search">Search</h2>

<p>
Search finds manuscript images based on transcribed text from the <%= link_to 'editions currently available', "#{about_path}#editions" %> in EDA. 
Greater relevance is given to matches in the <%= link_to 'first line or title', "#{faq_path}#3" %> and to words that occur multiple times within a poem.
</p>
<h3>Search Results</h3>
<p>
Search results display information about each manuscript: 
<%= link_to 'first line or title', "#{faq_path}#3" %>, presumed <%= link_to 'date', "#{faq_path}#4" %> and recipient (if provided), and a reference number for each work related to the image&mdash;
according to the <%= link_to 'edition or library', about_path %> that provided the information.
</p>
<h3>Options and Sorting</h3>
<p>
By default, search finds manuscript images using full text from all available <%= link_to 'editions', "#{about_path}#editions" %> and <%= link_to 'libraries', team_path %>. 
Search results can be limited to a single edition or library&mdash;or a specific piece of information, such as first line&mdash;
before or after searching. Search results can be sorted by selecting the heading of each column in the main search results view.
</p>

<h2 id="images">Manuscript Images</h2>

<p>
EDA makes high-resolution images of manuscripts of Dickinson&rsquo;s poetry available. Unavailable images&mdash;
which may include Dickinson manuscripts that have been described or transcribed by others but are presumed lost or destroyed, or forthcoming images from the project&rsquo;s growing list of partners and collaborators&mdash;
are represented by a placeholder image taken from <i><%= link_to raw( 'Emily Dickinson&rsquo;s Herbarium' ), resources_path %></i>.
</p>
<h3>Enlarging</h3>
<p>
To magnify manuscript images, double-click the image or use the &ldquo;Zoom In&rdquo; icon.
The &ldquo;Zoom Out&rdquo; icon reduces; the &ldquo;Go home&rdquo; icon returns to default size; 
and &ldquo;Full Page&rdquo; fills the screen with the image; clicking again or hitting &ldquo;Esc&rdquo; returns to the original view.
</p>
