<h3>Saving and Annotating</h3>
<p>
Open the &ldquo;My Notes&rdquo; tab to write and save your own annotations on each image page.
Open &ldquo;Save to Reading List&rdquo; to create one or more lists of images to order and revisit. 
To save notes or reading lists, you will need to <%= link_to 'sign up/sign in', new_user_session_url %> to EDA.
</p>
<h3>Downloading</h3>
To download a large version of the image and its associated metadata and credits, use the &ldquo;Save&rdquo; icon. 
The image will download as an uncompressed file, 1200 pixels wide at 96dpi, approximately 1-2MB in file size. 
To request larger files, contact the owning library. 
Image attribution&mdash;
<i>which must be included whenever the image is used under the terms of the Creative Commons license for this site</i>&mdash;
will download as a separate text file 
(consult information about EDA <%= link_to 'Copyright & Terms of Use', terms_path %>).
</p>
<h3>Page Turning and Reading View</h3>
<p>
&ldquo;Reading View&rdquo; shows facing pages and simulates physical page-turning with interactive animation. &ldquo;Manuscript View&rdquo; shows a single page with tools to inspect the image, text to compare, and new or related search options. &ldquo;Previous Page&rdquo; and &ldquo;Next Page&rdquo; move between manuscript images in order. The order of pages is determined by the edition or library context you choose. When browsing by image, library order is the default; when searching or browsing by work, edition order is the default. The default order can be changed using the &ldquo;Page Order&rdquo; menu. The edition page order reflects Franklin fascicle order or your own order (if you have signed in and created an edition).
</p>

